definitions.820-3476: What is 820-3476? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.
definitions.U1950: What is U1950? This chip often becomes corroded on pin 8 on the PP3V42_G3H pin causing PM_SLP_S4_L to go missing.
definitions.U7090: What is U7090? This chip is often responsible for creating PP3V42_G3H.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-3476</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> cpu vcore 1.759V
threads.message:
Liquid damage.
had missing <CHIP>U7090</CHIP> pin and crap under smc.

After fixing <CHIP>U7090</CHIP> and smc macbook turned on.

No idea what happened but now all rails fine only cpu vcore 1.759V

Tried replacing <CHIP>U1900</CHIP> and <CHIP>U1950</CHIP>
